This paper is a review of the evolutionary history of deep learning models, which is a topic that spans multiple sub-fields of computer science. However, given the focus on neural networks and their development, cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the models' applications in computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL), which are both relevant sub-categories. Additionally, the paper touches on the theoretical aspects of deep learning, such as model complexity and optimization, which are relevant to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
